<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1438,186,599]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,482,186,212]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Comments and Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[491,765,186,211]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lophopedia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buchwaldi">
<emphasis box="[491,765,186,211]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lophopedia buchwaldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the remaining species by the narrowly rounded omaulus (
<figureCitation box="[493,584,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 − 33" captionStartId="12.[151,270,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,186,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,186,1456]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 31 − 33. Lophopedia buchwaldi (Cockerell), paralectotype female (AMNH). Fig. 31: head, frontal view; Fig. 32: lateral view, white arrow indicate the acute angle of the omaulus; Fig. 33: dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189423/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Fig. 
<number box="[550,584,225,251]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
), almost carinate, and frons with dense minute punctures intermingled with coarse punctures on disc (
<figureCitation box="[519,608,264,290]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 − 33" captionStartId="12.[151,270,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,186,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,186,1456]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 31 − 33. Lophopedia buchwaldi (Cockerell), paralectotype female (AMNH). Fig. 31: head, frontal view; Fig. 32: lateral view, white arrow indicate the acute angle of the omaulus; Fig. 33: dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189423/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Fig. 
<number box="[575,608,264,290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
). The omaulus of 
<taxonomicName box="[825,1097,264,289]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lophopedia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buchwaldi">
<emphasis box="[825,1097,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lophopedia buchwaldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the carina of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lophopedia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">L. pygmaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the angle very weak and short, occupying less than one third of the upper portion of mesepisternum, and the mandible of the female has only one preapical tooth. This species is only known from the two females of the 
<typeStatus box="[421,472,380,406]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
series. 
<taxonomicName box="[562,832,380,405]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lophopedia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buchwaldi">
<emphasis box="[562,832,380,405]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lophopedia buchwaldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably closely related to 
<emphasis box="[1188,1429,380,405]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName box="[1188,1316,380,405]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lophopedia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">L. apicalis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1328,1429,380,405]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lophopedia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">L. minor</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[200,345,418,443]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Lophopedia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraensis">
<emphasis box="[200,345,418,443]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">L. paraensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, judging by the sparsely punctured mesepisternum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
